reviewText: Everything expected

I wish it had more Elmo. My daughter loves anything with Elmo but is bored by all the clips that didn't have Elmo in it. Its not bad but we have to skip through about 1/2 of the clips since they don't have Elmo.
What can I say, you can't go wrong with Elmo.
Fun movie with lots of music

It's a 2016 dvd release date with footage from a LONG time ago. i thought i was getting a new movie that kids would enjoy, but instead got videos of kids from the 70s/80s? not cool.
Terrible  !!!!!

Love that we have this in our video library for our 2 year old.  Its long enough to keep him entertained without driving us nuts with the repetition!

Absolutely amazing. The cinematography and acting are second to none. The singing is angelic. Please do yourself and your family a favor and watch this show 70 times like us!
One of my son's favorites!

Grandson loves it.

I bought this for my daughter who now likes Elmo. There are definitely some parts where she "checks out" and others which engage her a lot. She enjoys music so this video provides more of that than other Elmo videos.

Waste of money. It starts off with singing and newer looking Elmo clips and ends up in a mash up of old Sesame Street episodes from the early nineties and has hardly any singing. My toddler lost interest within 2 minutes.
Didn't grab my daughters attention
this is my grandaughters fav dvd
If you're looking for a video for your kids to watch that is mostly music this is not it this is like a normal episode. Whose main theme is almost music
Disapointed
My grandchild is glued!
great movie

I bought this video for my 16-month old son because it has the word "sing" in the title.  He hates the car, and the only thing that keeps him semi-happy are videos with lots of music.  I was so disappointed to find that most of the music is concentrated at the beginning of the movie, and the rest is just random Sesame Street scenes put together to make a "movie."  He hates it.  NOT worth $10.
Long running which is nice.  My 2 yr old grandson likes it.
